{"questionId":"9074598","questionHtml":"<p>Two blocks, X and Y, are placed in contact with each other. Data for the blocks are provided.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/8799e8c92aa80167720038a4fdd893f95073b81f.png\"></p>\n<p>X has a mass <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math></em>. What is the mass of Y?</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo> </mo><mi>m</mi></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo> </mo><mi>m</mi></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>C</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9074598","referenceCode":"22M.1.SL.TZ1.11","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Two blocks, X and Y, are placed in contact with each other. Data for the blocks are provided. X has a mass m. What is the mass of Y? A. m4 B. m C. 4 m D. 6 m","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"11","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 3: Thermal physics","3.1 – Thermal concepts","Core","Topic 3: Thermal physics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}